    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <actionDate>2017-03-27</actionDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-05-30T15:49:12Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <updateDate>2017-03-27T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill authorizes the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC), upon request, to extend by six years the time period during which construction must commence on the Gathright Hydroelectric Project located in Alleghany County, Virginia, and the Flannagan Dam and Reservoir Hydroelectric Project located in Dickenson County, Virginia.</p> <p>Additionally, FERC may reinstate either construction license if it is expired.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
        <item>
          <name>Reported to Senate without amendment</name>
          <actionDesc>Reported to Senate without amendment</actionDesc>
          <actionDate>2017-05-24</actionDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-06-15T16:04:13Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <versionCode>80</versionCode>
          <updateDate>2017-05-24T12:38:59Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary has been expanded because action occurred on the measure.)</p> <p>(Sec.1)This bill authorizes the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC), upon request, to extend by six years the time period during which construction must commence on the Gathright Hydroelectric Project located in Alleghany County, Virginia, and the Flannagan Dam and Reservoir Hydroelectric Project located in Dickenson County, Virginia.</p> <p>Additionally, FERC may reinstate either construction license if it is expired.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
